transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello, I wanted to call to cancel my subscription, please.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me pull that prescription here.

Speaker 2: Mr. Richard Kroger?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I see that Dr. Olcom wrote a prescription for Viagra, 100 mg, 10 tablets, every 30 days for you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but I wanted...

Speaker 1: They don't work and I don't want any more.

Speaker 2: I just want to cancel it.

Speaker 1: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 2: If you don't need them, if they don't work, we can send you some things to try that can help you.

Speaker 1: I don't know if it's your first time taking Viagra.

Speaker 2: Did you try Cialis?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I've done all the rest of them, too.

Speaker 2: I just want to cancel, please.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay, no problem.

Speaker 2: So, I'm canceling the doctor prescription here for you.

Speaker 1: We could have paused the account and you could have reordered as needed.

Speaker 2: You declined.

Speaker 1: You declined the replacement.

Speaker 2: Just be advised, if anything's changed, price will be different if the company take the order

Speaker 1: because we just lost the consultation they financed for you.

Speaker 2: I understand.

Speaker 1: And they tried to do that one time.

Speaker 2: No, no, that's good.

Speaker 1: Everything is settled for you, Mr. Kroger.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
